The paper deals with natural language processing and database querying, which are both topics within the scope of computer science. Specifically, it focuses on neural text-to-SQL generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also utilizes type information to better understand rare entities and numbers in natural language questions, which involves database schema and metadata, falling under the category of databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to the problem, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and utilizes content from databases to improve performance, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
